#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code stack me minimum element ko O(1) time me track karne ke liye encoding technique use karta hai.

1. Ek variable minEle maintain karte hain jo current minimum store karta hai.
2. Normal push:
   - Agar new element >= minEle hai, to normal push kar do.
3. Agar new element < minEle hai:
   - To stack me original value nahi push karte,
     balki encoded value push karte hain: (2*x - minEle)
   - Aur minEle = x update kar dete hain.
4. Pop operation:
   - Agar popped value < minEle hai,
     iska matlab ye encoded value hai.
     To original previous minimum nikalte hain:
     previousMin = (2*minEle - encodedValue)
     Aur minEle update kar dete hain.
5. getMin():
   - Direct minEle return kar dete hain.

Main idea:
Jab bhi new minimum aata hai, hum stack me encoded value store karte hain
taaki previous minimum bhi recover kar sakein pop ke time.

Is technique se extra stack use nahi hota aur getMin O(1) me milta hai.

Time Complexity: O(1) for push, pop, getMin
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

import java.util.Stack;

class MyStack {
    int minEle;
    Stack<Integer> s;

    MyStack() {
        //You can code here
        s = new Stack<>();
    }

    int getMin() {
        //You can code here
        if(s.isEmpty()) return -1;
        return minEle;

    }

    int pop() {
        //You can code here
        if(s.isEmpty()) return -1;

        int y = s.pop();
        if(y < minEle){
          int nextMin = (2*minEle) - y;
          int temp = minEle;
          minEle = nextMin;
          return temp;
        }
        else{
          return y;
        }

    }

    void push(int x) {
        //You can code here        
        if(s.isEmpty()){
          minEle = x;
          s.push(x);
          return;
        }
        if(x < minEle){
          s.push((2*x)-minEle);
          minEle = x;
        }
        else{
          s.push(x);
        }

    }
}
